-ups'),(4927,692,'_individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4928,692,'individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-description','<p>Our consulting physician is a long-time addiction specialist, and is able to prescribe and\r\n                            manage medications to best treat any\r\n                            accompanying medical issues.\r\n                        </p>'),(4929,692,'_individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4930,692,'individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-image','2918'),(4931,692,'_individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4932,692,'individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4933,692,'_individual-section-item_2_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4934,692,'individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-title','Case Management'),(4935,692,'_individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4936,692,'individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-description',' <p>It is our strong belief that those suffering from addiction need an\r\n                            advocate through the difficult process of early recovery. These early days can be consuming\r\n                            and overwhelming. People need someone who is\r\n                            knowledgeable; who can provide help, guidance, knowledge and support through this difficult\r\n                            time; who can provide comfort and support while the addict focuses on what is most important\r\n                            – their recovery. We provide each client with full and comprehensive case management\r\n                            throughout the entire treatment process: from the first phone call and consultation, to\r\n                            aftercare. We are there every step of the way. </p>'),(4937,692,'_individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4938,692,'individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-image','2919'),(4939,692,'_individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4940,692,'individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4941,692,'_individual-section-item_3_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4942,692,'individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-title','Group Counseling'),(4943,692,'_individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4944,692,'individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-description','<p>Group counseling sessions serve as a core aspect of successful alcohol and drug addiction\r\n                            treatment. Group sessions cover a variety of topics such as addiction education, relapse\r\n                            prevention, relationships, and life skills. Groups take place daily, Monday to Friday, and\r\n                            provide safe, structured environments where people can learn about their addiction and\r\n                            receive support and encouragement from others who are also in treatment. All of our groups\r\n                            are run by licensed or certified therapists and counselors who specialize in treating\r\n                            addiction. </p>'),(4945,692,'_individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4946,692,'individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-image','2920'),(4947,692,'_individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4948,692,'individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4949,692,'_individual-section-item_4_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4950,692,'individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-title','Individual Counseling'),(4951,692,'_individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4952,692,'individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-description','<p>Individual counseling sessions provide clients with the opportunity to educate themselves\r\n                            about\r\n                            their addiction and work on ways to sustain successful recovery in a one-on-one setting with\r\n                            a\r\n                            licensed therapists, certified chemical dependency counselors, and job counselors.\r\n                            Therapists,\r\n                            counselors and clients collaborate and work together to develop ways to maintain sobriety,\r\n                            prevent relapse, and build a full, responsible life. Each client receives at least one\r\n                            one-on-one session per week. </p>'),(4953,692,'_individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4954,692,'individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-image','2921'),(4955,692,'_individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4956,692,'individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4957,692,'_individual-section-item_5_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4958,692,'individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-title','Family and Couples Counseling'),(4959,692,'_individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4960,692,'individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-description','<p>The disease of addiction does not only affect the individual abusing the substance, but the\r\n                            entire family as well. Family groups and private family counseling sessions can provide the\r\n                            addict and his or her loved ones with an opportunity to work on the process of recovery\r\n                            together. What often gets lost in the fights, disagreements, and conflict that often\r\n                            accompany\r\n                            the disease of addiction is the underlying love that family members have for one another.\r\n                            Family\r\n                            counseling sessions\r\n                            provide opportunities for loved ones to connect and fight the illness together, increasing\r\n                            the\r\n                            chances for sustained recovery. </p>'),(4961,692,'_individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4962,692,'individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-image','2922'),(4963,692,'_individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4964,692,'individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-over-description','  <div class=\"out-text-area\">\r\n                    <p>Family groups and private sessions take place every Saturday, along with a fun family outing,\r\n                        which gives everyone a chance to get to know other people who’ve been through what they are\r\n                        going through, and receive support. </p>\r\n                </div>'),(4965,692,'_individual-section-item_6_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4966,692,'individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-title','Recreational Activities'),(4967,692,'_individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4968,692,'individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-description','<p>At Alo House Outpatient, we provide our clients with opportunities for numerous experiential\r\n                            and\r\n                            recreational outings. These include yoga, hiking, working out, horseback riding, stand up\r\n                            paddle\r\n                            boarding, volunteering, martial arts lessons, and other fun excursions. We believe that\r\n                            getting\r\n                            people involved in these activities increases the body’s natural endorphin systems, which in\r\n                            turn provide people with a substitute for the soothing ‘pleasure and reward’ properties that\r\n                            alcohol and drugs once provided them with. We believe that helping to get people into their\r\n                            bodies, and out into the world, developing a sense of purpose and connection, is a key to\r\n                            recovery from alcohol and drug addiction. </p>'),(4969,692,'_individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4970,692,'individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-image','2923'),(4971,692,'_individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4972,692,'individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4973,692,'_individual-section-item_7_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4974,692,'individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-title','Drug Testing Program'),(4975,692,'_individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4976,692,'individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-description','<p>Comprehensive drug monitoring is an integral component to our\r\n                            Outpatient clients’ care. The level of accountability that is provided by frequent and\r\n                            highly\r\n                            accurate drug testing virtually guarantees that our clients stay sober as long as they\r\n                            belong to\r\n                            our monitoring\r\n                            program. Alo House has partnered with a toxicology laboratory, which – with their\r\n                            state-of-the-art liquid chromatography-mass\r\n                            spectrometry instrumentation and automated laboratory testing\r\n                            processes – provides us with fast and accurate quantitative results.</p>'),(4977,692,'_individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4978,692,'individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-image','2924'),(4979,692,'_individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4980,692,'individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4981,692,'_individual-section-item_8_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4982,692,'individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-title','Professionals Rehab Program'),(4983,692,'_individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4984,692,'individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-description','  <p>Alo House offers a ‘Professionals Program,’ geared toward those who have either not lost\r\n                            their\r\n                            jobs, who are wanting to re-enter their profession, or who are otherwise considered ‘high\r\n                            functioning.’ The sober living facility that houses those in the professional program is\r\n                            designed to suit an adult, executive clientele. The recovery program takes place during\r\n                            three\r\n                            nights in the evening, from 6pm until 9pm, and one weekend day. This schedule reflects the\r\n                            fact\r\n                            that people are busy putting their professional houses back in order during daytime\r\n                            hours. </p>'),(4985,692,'_individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4986,692,'individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-image','2925'),(4987,692,'_individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4988,692,'individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-over-description',''),(4989,692,'_individual-section-item_9_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4990,692,'individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-title','Young Adult Program'),(4991,692,'_individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-title','field_5aa400700fa96'),(4992,692,'individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-description','<p>Historically, drug and alcohol treatment centers have been geared toward middle-aged\r\n                            professionals. The trend, however, has been that more and more young people are entering\r\n                            treatment for addiction. The treatment industry has been slow to adapt to this changing\r\n                            demographic picture. In particular, there is a widespread problem today of young people who\r\n                            are\r\n                            experiencing a ‘failure to launch,’ who have no experience in the work force, or with any of\r\n                            the\r\n                            basic\r\n                            responsibilities of adulthood. Becoming employed around the age of 17 is an extremely\r\n                            important\r\n                            developmental milestone that is not being hit by young people today. This problem needs to\r\n                            be\r\n                            addressed head-on in this new era of chemical dependency treatment. </p>'),(4993,692,'_individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-description','field_5aa4007d0fa97'),(4994,692,'individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-image','2926'),(4995,692,'_individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-image','field_5aa4009e0fa98'),(4996,692,'individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-over-description','<p>At Alo House Outpatient, it is our job to help get our younger clients up and running and\r\n                        functioning in the adult world. We do this by teaching them practical life-skills, and\r\n                        accelerating their transformation into adulthood. We believe that we are either reinforcing the\r\n                        problem of ‘learned helplessness’ that so many young people today suffer from, or we are helping\r\n                        them to achieve a state of autonomy. The heart of our work is geared toward helping our young\r\n                        clients achieve the freedom to live their own lives. And we make sure to have some fun in the\r\n                        process — without joy, a sober life is next to impossible. </p>'),(4997,692,'_individual-section-item_10_individual-section-item-over-description','field_5aa40ba092838'),(4998,2927,'title','Intensive Outpatient Program'),(4999,2927,'_title','field_5aa3e61a71386'),(5000,2927,'description','<pre>&lt;p&gt;After discharging from a residential treatment program, individuals are able to begin the next stage\r\n    of their journey at the next lowest level of care, at our Alo House Outpatient program. Many of our\r\n    clients live in a local sober living home. We work with a preferred network of sober living\r\n    operators who we believe maintain a high standard of quality in the provision of safe, alcohol- and\r\n    drug-free environments.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;The length of time in Alo House Outpatient program will vary, depending on individual needs. Some of\r\n    the more intensive therapeutic work occurs in the outpatient phase of treatment, since the client is\r\n    ready to go deeper into the roots of their emotional disturbances only after the fog associated with\r\n    the first few weeks of being clean and sober has lifted.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Outpatient group and one-on-one therapy is the continuation of the work that people began with their\r\n    therapists in the inpatient setting. During their time at the Alo House Outpatient program, clients\r\n    will be challenged with more advanced concepts, and given more of the important, concrete tools\r\n    they’ll need to flourish and thrive in their lives. A focus will be placed upon ‘launching’ the\r\n    client, and transitioning them into life after treatment.&lt;/p&gt;</pre>'),(5001,2927,'_description','field_5aa3e76771387'),(5002,2927,'top-section-title','Intensive Outpatient Program'),(5003,2927,'_top-section-title','field_5aa3e61a71386'),(5004,2927,'top-section-description','<p>After discharging from a residential treatment program, individuals are able to begin the next stage\r\n    of their journey at the next lowest level of care, at our Alo House Outpatient program. Many of our\r\n    clients live in a local sober living home. We work with a preferred network of sober living\r\n    operators who we believe maintain a high standard of quality in the provision of safe, alcohol- and\r\n    drug-free environments.</p>\r\n<p>The length of time in Alo House Outpatient program will vary, depending on individual needs. Some of\r\n    the more intensive therapeutic work occurs in the outpatient phase of treatment, since the client is\r\n    ready to go deeper into the roots of their emotional disturbances only after the fog associated with\r\n    the first few weeks of being clean and sober has lifted.</p>\r\n<p>Outpatient group and one-on-one therapy is the continuation of the work that people began with their\r\n    therapists in the inpatient setting. During their time at the Alo House Outpatient program, clients\r\n    will be challenged with more advanced concepts, and given more of the important, concrete tools\r\n    they’ll need to flourish and thrive in their lives. A focus will be placed upon ‘launching’ the\r\n    client, and transitioning them into life after treatment.</p>'),(5005,2927,'_top-section-description','field_5aa3e76771387'),(5006,2927,'location-section-title','Our Location'),(5007,2927,'_location-section-title','field_5aa3ef2d06f25'),(5008,29