INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4,1,'2013-11-04 19:32:01','2013-11-04 19:32:01','','Home','','publish','open','open','','home','','','2017-12-21 21:16:25','2017-12-21 21:16:25','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=4',40,'page','',0),(9,1,'2013-11-04 20:26:15','2013-11-04 20:26:15','Jared motherfucking valentine','IMG_3379','This would be some caption text','inherit','open','open','','img_3379','','','2013-11-04 20:26:15','2013-11-04 20:26:15','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_3379.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(11,1,'2013-11-04 20:32:34','2013-11-04 20:32:34','','IMG_3383','','inherit','open','open','','img_3383','','','2013-11-04 20:32:34','2013-11-04 20:32:34','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_3383.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(14,1,'2013-11-04 22:46:47','2013-11-04 22:46:47','','we_accept_insurance','','inherit','open','open','','we_accept_insurance','','','2013-11-04 22:46:47','2013-11-04 22:46:47','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/we_accept_insurance.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(15,1,'2013-11-04 22:46:47','2013-11-04 22:46:47','','credit_logos','','inherit','open','open','','credit_logos','','','2013-11-04 22:46:47','2013-11-04 22:46:47','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/credit_logos.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(16,1,'2013-11-04 23:24:59','2013-11-04 23:24:59','Evan is a Co-Founder of Alo House, and specializes in admissions, and marketing and business development.  An active participant in the recovery world, it felt natural for Evan to transition into the sober living business, and help others obtain and maintain sobriety.  In 2010, he and Jared founded Alo House, which, in less than three years, became one of the most successful sober living residences in the area.  Evan has a natural ability to connect with clients, and bring out a sense of hope in them.\n\nEvan has a Master\'s Degree in Community Development Planning from the University of British Columbia.  His strong academic background, coupled with years of hands-on experience doing community-organizing work with non-profits, makes him a great asset to the Alo House team.  An example of this is the \'Alo House Farms\' project, an exercise in community economic development.  It gives clients valuable work experience in a variety of areas, while simultaneously building their self-esteem, as they feel part of something larger than themselves, and positively affects those around them.\n\nEvan has been sober since November 2nd, 2005.','Evan Haines','','publish','closed','closed','','evan-haines','','','2013-11-04 23:24:59','2013-11-04 23:24:59','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=staff&amp;p=16',18,'staff','',0),(23,1,'2013-11-05 19:11:26','2013-11-05 19:11:26','','Treatment Program','','publish','open','open','','treatment-program','','','2018-03-12 07:33:56','2018-03-12 07:33:56','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=23',39,'page','',0),(27,1,'2013-11-05 19:11:47','2013-11-05 19:11:47','<h2>Teen Drug And Alcohol Treatment</h3>\n<a href=\"http://paradigmmalibu.com/\"><img alt=\"paradigm-logo-300x47\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/paradigm-logo-300x47.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"47\" /></a>\n<h2>Drug and Alcohol Treatment</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.themeadows.org/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/meadows-logo.png\" /></a>\n<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http://www.milestonesranch.com/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.milestonesranch.com/images/milestones-ranch-malibu.png\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Alcoholics Anonymous</h2>\n<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/img/aa-logo.png\" /></td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align: middle;\"><a href=\"http://aa.org\">AA.org</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Cocaine Anonymous</h2>\n<a href=\"http://http://www.ca.org/\">Cocaine Anonymous Website</a>\n<h2>Narcotics Anonymous</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.na.org/\">Narcotics Anonymous Website</a>\n<h2>Malibu AA Meetings</h2>\n<a href=\"http://simeetings.com/LA/MalibuMtgs.html\">SIM Meetings - Malibu AA Meeting Schedule.</a>\n<h2>Free AA Speaker MP3\'s</h2>\n<a href=\"http://xa-speakers.org\">xa-speakers.org – AA Speaker mp3’s</a>\n<h2>Los Angeles Sober Living Coalition Member</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.soberhousing.net/\"><img alt=\"sober-coalition\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/sober-coalition.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"139\" /></a>\n<h2>Map of Local Malibu Hikes</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.hikespeak.com/los-angeles/santa-monica-mountains/\">hikespeak.com</a>','Resources','','publish','open','open','','resources','','','2013-11-05 19:11:47','2013-11-05 19:11:47','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=27',37,'page','',0),(33,1,'2013-11-05 19:12:11','2013-11-05 19:12:11','[gallery link=\"file\" size=\"medium\" captions=\"hide\" ids=\"2377,2378,2380,2382,2388,2386,2385,2636,2384,2637,1672,2383,2381,2365,2379,2375,2373,2368,2366,2370,2371,1994,2372,2338,2012,2339,2340,1675,2341,2343,2020,2344,1995,2345,2346,2342,2347,2348,2349,2350,2053,2351,2352,2052,2353,2354,2359,2364,2363,2358,2357,2007,2362,2361,2360,2356,1979,1997,2022,2056,2055,2355,2054,1899,1904,1829,1834,1853,1835,1798,1738,1727\"]','Photos','','publish','open','open','','photos','','','2013-11-05 19:12:11','2013-11-05 19:12:11','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=33',36,'page','',0),(35,1,'2013-11-05 19:12:21','2013-11-05 19:12:21','<p class=\"lead\">The bravest thing anyone can ever do is reach out and ask for help. We know how difficult this can be. We want this part of your journey to be as painless as possible.</p>\n\nSo if you or a loved one call us today, you will be warmly greeted with the helping hand of someone who really cares. Whether you choose Alo House or not, we will assist you in navigating the sometimes confusing terrain of the drug treatment world, and help to point you in the right direction.\n<p>Connect with someone at Alo House right now.</p>\n<p>Call (888) 595-0235 or email us <a href=\"mailto:info@alorecovery.com\">info@alorecovery.com</a></p>\n</div>','Contact','','publish','open','open','','contact','','','2013-11-05 19:12:21','2013-11-05 19:12:21','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=35',38,'page','',0),(48,1,'2013-11-05 23:21:27','2013-11-05 23:21:27','','IMG_3468','','inherit','open','open','','img_3468','','','2013-11-05 23:21:27','2013-11-05 23:21:27','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_3468.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(50,1,'2013-11-05 23:22:04','2013-11-05 23:22:04','','IMG_3776','','inherit','open','open','','img_3776','','','2013-11-05 23:22:04','2013-11-05 23:22:04','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_3776.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(52,1,'2013-11-05 23:22:57','2013-11-05 23:22:57','','IMG_4031','','inherit','open','open','','img_4031','','','2013-11-05 23:22:57','2013-11-05 23:22:57','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_4031.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(54,1,'2013-11-05 23:23:24','2013-11-05 23:23:24','','IMG_4088-Edit','','inherit','open','open','','img_4088-edit','','','2013-11-05 23:23:24','2013-11-05 23:23:24','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_4088-Edit.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(56,1,'2013-11-05 23:23:51','2013-11-05 23:23:51','','IMG_4229','','inherit','open','open','','img_4229','','','2013-11-05 23:23:51','2013-11-05 23:23:51','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_4229.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(58,1,'2013-11-05 23:24:17','2013-11-05 23:24:17','','IMG_4311','','inherit','open','open','','img_4311','','','2013-11-05 23:24:17','2013-11-05 23:24:17','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_4311.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(70,1,'2013-11-07 00:44:53','2013-11-07 00:44:53','“Alo House is a great treatment environment and transitional living situation. Living at Alo House, I am learning to live a healthy, fun, and sober lifestyle. At Alo House, I can grow and develop as a person and in my sobriety. The staff is very friendly and supportive, and made me feel welcome since the day I arrived. Alo House is like a family, and a place I can call home.”','Mitch A., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','mitch-a-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:44:53','2013-11-07 00:44:53','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=70',64,'testimonials','',0),(71,1,'2013-11-07 00:45:17','2013-11-07 00:45:17','“Alo House helped me become a contributing member of society, and made me appreciate life in ways I never had before. The owners have a very gentle approach and a kind attitude. Alo House is not just a sober living, it is my home.”','Eliot R., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','eliot-r-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:45:17','2013-11-07 00:45:17','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=71',63,'testimonials','',0),(72,1,'2013-11-07 00:45:40','2013-11-07 00:45:40','“In looking for the best place with and for our daughter, we wanted a residence that was serious in its approach by insisting on a zero tolerance approach, while at the same time combining a compassionate and welcoming atmosphere with all the right support. Alo House, through the personal and caring involvement of its owners, proved to be exactly the right combination of both.”','Anonymous, Parent','','publish','closed','closed','','anonymous-parent','','','2013-11-07 00:45:40','2013-11-07 00:45:40','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=72',62,'testimonials','',0),(73,1,'2013-11-07 00:46:10','2013-11-07 00:46:10','“My daughter has been at Alo House for the last few months. She has found it to be a very caring and healing community. As a parent, I have found Alo House to be very professionally run, by people who really care and who are very aware of, and responsive to, the needs of their clients and their families.”','Paul C., Parent','','publish','closed','closed','','paul-c-parent','','','2013-11-07 00:46:10','2013-11-07 00:46:10','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=73',61,'testimonials','',0),(74,1,'2013-11-07 00:46:54','2013-11-07 00:46:54','“I’ve been involved with Alo House in a number and capacities, and most importantly, I trust them. They walk the talk. They care about their clients, they create a safe home with structure, fun, caring and very capable staff. They are not punitive, but they have rules and boundaries that promote long-term recovery. They go above and beyond to be of service to their clients, and are real people you can relate to. I’ve worked with many people and places in the Southern California recovery community, and I wouldn’t send a person seeking treatment anywhere else but Alo House.”','Julie M., MFT, Therapist','','publish','closed','closed','','julie-m-mft-therapist','','','2013-11-07 00:46:54','2013-11-07 00:46:54','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=74',60,'testimonials','',0),(75,1,'2013-11-07 00:47:14','2013-11-07 00:47:14','“At first, I was hesitant to move into a sober living. However, I quickly felt comfortable and at ease living at Alo House. The staff and current clients made me feel like I was part of a family, rather than just a resident living in the house. I saw how active and full of life everyone was, which provided me with a great incentive to stay sober. I kept prolonging my stay at Alo House, and lived at the house a total of nine months! Every month got better and better; and I got stronger and stronger. I built a great network of sober friends and had a tremendous amount of help transitioning back out into the world on my own. It truly is a really special place; and I am so blessed to have found it.”\n','Olivia G., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','olivia-g-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:47:14','2013-11-07 00:47:14','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=75',59,'testimonials','',0),(76,1,'2013-11-07 00:47:35','2013-11-07 00:47:35','“These guys, they create an environment for healing. Do you want to heal? This is the place to do it. This is what these guys do, this is their skill-set. If someone wants to heal, they need a safe environment. They have created an environment where people feel safe.”','Daniel Marra, Certified Healing Touch International Practitioner','','publish','closed','closed','','daniel-marra-certified-healing-touch-international-practitioner','','','2013-11-07 00:47:35','2013-11-07 00:47:35','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=76',58,'testimonials','',0),(77,1,'2013-11-07 00:47:55','2013-11-07 00:47:55','“Alo House is a great place. Clean house. Beautiful beach. Great staff. The guys really helped me out, and got me motivated to go to meetings. That’s what makes this home really special — the staff. The place is very family oriented. Everyone looks out for each other. This is a very strong motivation to stay sober.”','Nick G., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','nick-g-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:47:55','2013-11-07 00:47:55','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=77',57,'testimonials','',0),(78,1,'2013-11-07 00:48:10','2013-11-07 00:48:10','“It was a great environment to be in in my early sobriety. The staff really helped integrate me into a productive and happy lifestyle. I would recommend this to a friend. Excellent location, top-notch service. It’s just one of those places that isn’t age-specific, and has something for everyone, in terms of location and activities offered. And everyone who works there is super caring, and love what they do! Other than that, the house is REALLY nice, very well furnished, very comfortable. Gives you that ‘home’ kind of feeling. The house is full of love! Even though I’m an alumni, I still frequently visit and keep in contact with the people who I made connections with during my stay.”','John M., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','john-m-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:48:10','2013-11-07 00:48:10','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=78',56,'testimonials','',0),(79,1,'2013-11-07 00:48:27','2013-11-07 00:48:27','“Alo House is more than a business, it is a family. The staff approaches the challenges of clients in transition professionally and knowledgeably, and with compassion and real solutions… At Alo House, they not only talk the talk, they lead by example, demonstrating how a sober life can be rewarding and fun. They create a supportive atmosphere for the clients to succeed and to help the families as well. I highly recommend Alo House without reservation.”\n','Deborah G., Parent','','publish','closed','closed','','deborah-g-parent','','','2013-11-07 00:48:27','2013-11-07 00:48:27','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=79',55,'testimonials','',0),(80,1,'2013-11-07 00:48:50','2013-11-07 00:48:50','“We have been down a long road, finally settling in with Alo House. Before, my son was just a number. It was very stressful and frustrating to keep track of my son and be assured of his well being. The minute I started communicating with Alo House, I was amazed. They seem to care about my son as much as I do. Whether through texts, phone or email, I receive immediate response to my questions. All of my concerns are taken care of, as Alo House mentors my son along.\n\nThe most amazing thing about Alo House is that staff immediately got to know my son on a personal level, and created a plan for him at the house to encourage him and give him something to live for — in his case, allowing him to create things at the house where his interests and talents are, giving him a reason to wake up in the morning, allowing him to help others using his talents, working on positive progression during his healing process.\n\nBecause Alo House is a small facility, everyone interacts as a family. Bonds have been created that will last a lifetime for my son. And finally, I need to mention that that the actual facility is unbelievably beautiful — clean inside, well manicured lawns overlooking the ocean! Anyone would be lucky to live there.\n\nThank you so much for appearing in our lives. Alo House is the reason that I can now sleep at night, knowing my son is a part of your family, under your care.”','June R., Parent','','publish','closed','closed','','june-r-parent','','','2013-11-07 00:48:50','2013-11-07 00:48:50','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=80',54,'testimonials','',0),(81,1,'2013-11-07 00:49:09','2013-11-07 00:49:09','“All treatment centers are not created equal – I know this from the painful experiences of my daughter. I am so grateful for Alo House. My daughter describes it as a peaceful home with an extended family who will cry with her when she hurts and celebrate with her when she succeeds. It’s not just a business to these folks; the owners and staff are personally committed to each individual’s recovery. We are blessed to be part of this home where Rachel has the structure, compassion and emotional support she needs as she builds a wonderful new life as a sober young woman.”','Donna C., Rachel’s Mom','','publish','closed','closed','','donna-c-rachels-mom','','','2013-11-07 00:49:09','2013-11-07 00:49:09','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=81',53,'testimonials','',0),(82,1,'2013-11-07 00:49:26','2013-11-07 00:49:26','“In working with the addiction population over the last four years, I have seen a lot of treatment environments. Alo House stands out amongst the rest because it offers non-judgemental acceptance, communication, and community. This creates a safe environment for clients to integrate back into the world with confidence and support. Furthermore, the owners play a major role in the successful operation of the program. They take clients on many real life adventures, from hiking in the Santa Monica Mountains to experiencing Cirque Du Soleil for the first time… Alo House is a great choice for anyone serious about transforming their life.”','Jesse Hanson, MA (Clinical Psychology), MFTI','','publish','closed','closed','','jesse-hanson-ma-clinical-psychology-mfti','','','2013-11-07 00:49:26','2013-11-07 00:49:26','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=82',52,'testimonials','',0),(83,1,'2013-11-07 00:49:47','2013-11-07 00:49:47','“As a therapist working with clients in recovery, I’ve been able to rely on the professional and caring support Alo House sober living consistently offers my clients and their families. Management and staff genuinely care, which is evident by their commitment to making sure all clients have the structure, accountability and support needed to maintain sobriety, with the understanding of the importance in having fun and becoming part of the community. Alo House has continued to work closely with me when it comes to treatment plans and case management, which has been a necessary factor in achieving long term success. I would recommend Alo House sober living to anyone looking to launch themselves into a solid new way of life.”','Lyn R., MA, MFTI, Therapist at Milestones Ranch Malibu','','publish','closed','closed','','lyn-r-ma-mfti-therapist-at-milestones-ranch-malibu','','','2013-11-07 00:49:47','2013-11-07 00:49:47','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=83',51,'testimonials','',0),(84,1,'2013-11-07 00:50:12','2013-11-07 00:50:12','“My stay at Alo House was life-changing.  The staff and fellow clients had created a strong family-like bond, which they instantly welcomed me into.  The dedication of the staff helped me to form an enthusiastic and motivated view of not only my recovery, but also my life.  If I ever needed advice or direction, they were there.  The foundation created in treatment was solidified by the positive environment and acceptance I encountered during my stay at Alo House by the Sea.  I am truly grateful for that experience.”','Jacob S., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','jacob-s-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:50:12','2013-11-07 00:50:12','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=84',50,'testimonials','',0),(85,1,'2013-11-07 00:50:29','2013-11-07 00:50:29','“When I came to Alo House, I was a broken soul. It seemed like everywhere I went I was shortly rejected and misunderstood. I remember the first night I met Jared and Evan. As soon as I walked onto the Alo House property, I felt a sense of safety and serenity as they showed me around their beautiful house. Every day at Alo House was a spiritual awakening like I’ve never had at any other time of my life. In my humble opinion, the spiritual journey that you will find yourself walking every day wile at Alo House is going to be one that will change your life completely for the better. I now wake up every day happy and sober. My relationship with my family is completely healed and stronger than it has ever been and my life is so big. I love Alo House and I give them my highest recommendations to anyone.”','Gary W, Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','gary-w-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:50:29','2013-11-07 00:50:29','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=85',49,'testimonials','',0),(86,1,'2013-11-07 00:50:51','2013-11-07 00:50:51','“Alo House will always be my home away from home. The meals and food are amazing. We were fed very well! We got to experience our daily lives with a full support system in place, and a very positive vibe that makes you want to succeed in sobriety. The house is fun and active, and has a strong sense of community. I particularly enjoyed hiking and paddle boarding. Being right on the beach, there were always plenty of beach days. Once a week, we held male/female groups to check in. The morning meditation reading was a great way to jump start the day! We loved to do everything together. From going as a group to meetings, going to dinner as a family, we were always having fun!!!\n\nEvan and Jared are amazing men, who are there for anybody, at any time of the day or night. they are great influences, and a joy to be around. I can’t speak highly enough of my time at Alo House!”','Kelani C., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','kelani-c-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:50:51','2013-11-07 00:50:51','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=86',48,'testimonials','',0),(87,1,'2013-11-07 00:51:10','2013-11-07 00:51:10','“Dear Evan and Jared, this is just a note to let you both know that I am doing very well. My time at Alo House was very special. You and your staff are such loving, caring people. I felt at home and a part of the family, immediately. My three months at Alo House have given me such a good foundation going forward in my sobriety. Words cannot express my gratitude and how blessed I feel to have found Alo House. Thank you again. Love to you all.”\n','Doris S., Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','doris-s-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:51:10','2013-11-07 00:51:10','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=87',47,'testimonials','',0),(88,1,'2013-11-07 00:51:30','2013-11-07 00:51:30','“Alo House is five star all the way! The beautiful environment, the staff, and activities are simply a few of the items giving this home such a quality experience. Truly, it is the integrity of its programming, its structure, and its fidelity to sobriety — to providing a home where individuals can grow and evolve into productive sober adults as they reenter community!\n\nThank you Evan and Jared for your dedication to this important work!”','Debbie Briem, LMFT,  Therapist at Milestones Ranch Malibu','','publish','closed','closed','','debbie-briem-lmft-therapist-at-milestones-ranch-malibu','','','2013-11-07 00:51:30','2013-11-07 00:51:30','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=88',41,'testimonials','',0),(89,1,'2013-11-07 00:51:54','2013-11-07 00:51:54','“If you are reading this testimonial, know that I feel a profound compassion for you. Being the mother of an addict, I know what it feels like to have your heart broken and feel pain you never knew existed. Our daughter went to a highly acclaimed, world renowned rehabilitation center out of state. We were quickly educated on all of the different scenarios that can and or will happen when your ‘loved one’ leaves the structure of rehab. The single most important thing is their transition into ‘real world’ as a sober person. After trying several sober living environments for our daughter — all of which failed — we found Alo House.\n\nIt is hard to put into words the emotions and the intense joy we have experienced with Alo House over the past five months. Evan and Jared are doing it right.\n\nWe felt that if our daughter had the chance to become healthy — mind, body &amp; soul — she could make a decision of what kind of life she wanted for herself. The close working relationships Alo House Recovery Centers has with the professional community in and around Malibu have been instrumental in helping her navigate her way into a healthy, happy, sober lifestyle. Evan and Jared understand that in order to embrace a sober lifestyle, you need to be balanced in mind, body &amp; soul. They beautifully orchestrate this thru the use of SOBER FUN, healthy eating, therapy, meetings and being involved on a daily basis with each of the residents.\n\nEvan and Jared, and all staff members, lead by example. They truly care and invest the time to get to know all of the residents. The most remarkable thing about Alo House, and the thing that raises it to a level of its own, is the sense of family felt by ALL.\n\nI can honestly say that our family has grown and Alo House will always be a part of us. Please, feel free to call if you ever need to talk, 714-655-2765.”','Brigitte C., Parent','','publish','closed','closed','','brigitte-c-parent','','','2013-11-07 00:51:54','2013-11-07 00:51:54','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=89',46,'testimonials','',0),(90,1,'2013-11-07 00:52:18','2013-11-07 00:52:18','“We feel so lucky that our daughter found Alo House. Learning about addiction and what it takes to get sober is one thing. Discovering how to practice sobriety, no matter what, in the real world out there, is another – and this is where Alo House does such an impressive job. Our sense is that Alo House provides a healthy, loving family situation, full of compassion and without judgement. From the moment our daughter came to Alo House, we felt sure she was in a safe space to continue her recovery — and we have only become more and more certain of that, the more we learn. Evan and Jared clearly take each person from exactly where they are, and create an individualized path — an environment with just enough support and just enough challenge — so that each member gets what they need to make the transition to a clean and sober life. We, as parents, feel tremendously comforted by the sense of well-being and serious progress we feel from our daughter.”','Anonymous, Parents','','publish','closed','closed','','anonymous-parents','','','2013-11-07 00:52:18','2013-11-07 00:52:18','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=90',45,'testimonials','',0),(91,1,'2013-11-07 00:52:39','2013-11-07 00:52:39','“I have incredibly fond memories of Alo House. I arrived a slightly depressed, very miserable and incredibly guilty about what I have put my family through. Fast forward a few weeks, and I am not depressed ,I am looking forward to the future with some confidence and feeling better than I have in years. I embraced the program for the first time ever, and accept my lot in life. It is what it is, and I now have choices. I feel that the staff and owners all lead by example, and for me, that was so much more powerful than what I have experienced in rehab, which I always wanted to do my way. Perhaps I was just ready to change.  I often thought I could have just rented a house and done it myself, but then I remembered, I have tried that so many times, unsuccessfully. I needed whatever it is Alo House provided, and that something is really special … I miss my room which was a real haven for me.”','Anonymous, Alumni','','publish','closed','closed','','anonymous-alumni','','','2013-11-07 00:52:39','2013-11-07 00:52:39','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=91',44,'testimonials','',0),(92,1,'2013-11-07 00:53:03','2013-11-07 00:53:03','“The chemical dependency field, whether sober living or residential treatment, is filled with so many recovery choices.  Many offer luxury living — all the bells and whistles imaginable.  With all these choices, what is vital and important can get lost.  Alo House is the diamond in the rough. Its owners, Evan and Jared, have a vision, and not just one, they have a unique individualized vision for each person that walks through their doors.  Their approach encompasses seeing the whole person and their potential.  With this vision, they create a recovery community that loves each individual back to health and happiness. They know what is important, and when you meet them, you remember also.”','Karmen Kamla, MFT, Therapist','','publish','closed','closed','','karmen-kamla-mft-therapist','','','2013-11-07 00:53:03','2013-11-07 00:53:03','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=92',43,'testimonials','',0),(93,1,'2013-11-07 00:53:23','2013-11-07 00:53:23','“Alo House is what sober livings should all be. They help clients thrive in their recovery by reconnecting them to their spirit. They have helped my clients find the joy in recovery and a passion for their life! I am grateful that a place like Alo House exists!”','Noah Rothschild, MFT, Transformational Psychotherapist','','publish','closed','closed','','noah-rothschild-mft-transformational-psychotherapist','','','2013-11-07 00:53:23','2013-11-07 00:53:23','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=testimonials&amp;p=93',42,'testimonials','',0),(105,1,'2013-11-07 06:37:51','2013-11-07 06:37:51','Bob Forrest is perhaps best known as the straight talking, straight shooting counselor on VH1\'s Celebrity Rehab with Dr Drew. Bob had a long journey in his struggle with addiction, visiting rehab facilities 24 times before finding sobriety in 1996. He has spent the last 17 years being of service, becoming one of the foremost chemical dependency counselors working in the southern California region. For 5 years Bob was the clinical director and on the board for Musicians Assistance Program/MusiCares, and he spent 8 years counseling at Las Encinas Hospital in Pasadena. Bob\'s treatment philosophy and counseling services are brought to a client base that extends throughout the US as well as internationally. Bob can also be seen regularly on the CNN & HLN networks offering commentary as an addiction specialist.\n\nPrior to his life in recovery, Bob Forrest was best known as a musician, fronting the critically acclaimed Los Angeles bands: Thelonious Monster and The Bicycle Thief. Bob was heavily acclaimed for his gifts as a songwriter, and frontman. \n\nThelonious Monster was a key player in the hip Los Angeles music scene of the \'80s, playing innumerable shows along side The Red Hot Chili Peppers, Jane\'s Addiction, Fishbone, & Guns \'N Roses, among many others. Despite it\'s ever evolving lineup, the band released 5 lauded albums and notoriously performed at Holland\'s Pink Pop Festival in 1993.  \n\nBob\'s 2nd band, The Bicycle Thief, came together after Bob met a teenaged Josh Klinghoffer, a guitar prodigy who went on to become the guitarist in The Red Hot Chili Peppers. He also fronts his own band, Dot Hacker,  and was voted into the Rock N Roll Hall of fame as it\'s youngest member. The Bicycle Thief recorded one album, and released it twice, in different configurations. The Bicycle Thief played many shows at the notorious Viper Room, had a slot at the inaugural Coachella Festival and toured the US playing with The Red Hot Chili Peppers, The Foo Fighters, Stone Temple Pilots, and They Might Be Giants. Bob and Josh have both hinted that another album may come in the future. \n\nIn 2011 a documentary about Bob, “Bob And The Monster” premiered at SXSW and has since seen wide and home video release. In 2013 Bob’s memoir, “Running With Monsters” was published by Crown Books. He still performs on occasion with friends and members of his bands. ','Bob Forrest','','publish','closed','closed','','bob-forrest','','','2013-11-07 06:37:51','2013-11-07 06:37:51','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=staff&amp;p=105',2,'staff','',0),(111,1,'2013-11-07 06:39:59','2013-11-07 06:39:59','Alexis completed her schooling to become a chemical dependency counselor in October 2011. Since that time, she has worked at several treatment centers, and is currently completing her practicum hours. Alexis got sober at nineteen years old, after facing up to six years in the California State prison system due to her addiction to heroin. She presently writes for Vice Magazine about youth, addiction and recovery, and is also shooting a documentary for Vice, focusing on the heroin epidemic amongst youth in the Los Angeles area, and specifically, to show the human face of those in active addiction and hear their personal stories.','Alexis Haines','','publish','closed','closed','','alexis-neiers','','','2013-11-07 06:39:59','2013-11-07 06:39:59','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=staff&amp;p=111',14,'staff','',0),(112,1,'2013-11-07 06:40:19','2013-11-07 06:40:19','Jared is a Co-Founder of Alo House.  He is a Certified Developer and Operator of Sober Living Housing, and successfully operated Alo House sober living for a number of years before taking the company through the licensing process. Jared believed that it was time to offer a <span class=\"s1\">licensed substance use disorder and mental health program</span> at Alo House, that he had reached the limits of how he could effectively help people in the unregulated sober living field.  So he assembled a dream team of knowledgeable drug treatment providers and obtained licensure from the State of California’s Department of Health Care Services in order to better serve his clients.  Before Jared discovered his calling in the field of recovery, he worked as a producer and casting director in the film industry.  Even in this profession, Jared showed a remarkable sense of intuition and specialized in evaluating people and projects for collaborative effectiveness and creative development.  This collaborative, creative spirit has infused his work building Alo House into what it is today.','Jared Valentine','','publish','closed','closed','','jared-valentine','','','2013-11-07 06:40:19','2013-11-07 06:40:19','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?post_type=staff&amp;p=112',19,'staff','',0),(113,1,'2013-11-07 20:35:29','2013-11-07 20:35:29','','bob_forrest','','inherit','open','open','','bob_forrest','','','2013-11-07 20:35:29','2013-11-07 20:35:29','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/bob_forrest.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(114,1,'2013-11-07 20:35:30','2013-11-07 20:35:30','','danielle','','inherit','open','open','','danielle','','','2013-11-07 20:35:30','2013-11-07 20:35:30','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/danielle.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(115,1,'2013-11-07 20:35:30','2013-11-07 20:35:30','','evan_haines','','inherit','open','open','','evan_haines','','','2013-11-07 20:35:30','2013-11-07 20:35:30','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/evan_haines.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(116,1,'2013-11-07 20:35:31','2013-11-07 20:35:31','','jared_valentine','','inherit','open','open','','jared_valentine','','','2013-11-07 20:35:31','2013-11-07 20:35:31','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/jared_valentin