'image/jpeg',0),(203,1,'2013-11-08 01:24:42','2013-11-08 01:24:42','','alexis','','inherit','open','open','','alexis','','','2013-11-08 01:24:42','2013-11-08 01:24:42','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/alexis.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(204,1,'2013-11-08 01:25:44','2013-11-08 01:25:44','','sager','','inherit','open','open','','sager','','','2013-11-08 01:25:44','2013-11-08 01:25:44','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/sager.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(219,1,'2013-11-08 20:49:44','2013-11-08 20:49:44','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-298\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/images-1-250x187.jpg\" alt=\"images-1\" /><em>“I’ve been working with all kinds of addicts on a daily basis, in and out of formal rehab settings, for almost two decades now. As I’ve watched the quality of care in most of America’s rehabs deteriorate over the last few years,\n\nI have started working with a new, innovative, more cost-effective model. Basically, medical stabilization, followed by sober living, in conjunction with low-to-medium intensity out-patient treatment. In between detox and sober living, clients might spend a few weeks in a licensed treatment facility.\n\nCompared to the cost of the average rehab, this kind of alternative care has proved much less expensive, while at the same time, a good deal more effective. I have been amazed to watch client after client who I put through the new model achieving long-term sobriety, and at a much higher rate than I’ve ever seen in traditional rehab settings.  I began asking myself, ‘Why?’  Well, the answers are pretty simple.  On a whole, the clients are more hopeful and easier to work with.  It is obvious to me that this is because they feel they are really, finally accepting personal responsibility for their own recovery.  In other words, they are in a less restrictive living situation, a positive, supportive living environment, in which they have to really want sobriety, and be willing to do whatever is necessary to achieve and maintain it.  In this sort of an atmosphere, they aren’t just sitting around, but living free with their peers in a supportive, low-pressure, non-judgmental, hands-on recovery setting, a real home, in which they can actively participate in their own individual journeys into sobriety.\n\nFor me, the proof is in the results.  Each day, I look forward to fulfilling this vision though our work at Alo House, here in Malibu, California – one of the most inspiring, beautiful places on earth!\"\n</em>\n\n<h2>About Our Creative Director</h2>\nThe story of our Creative Director, Bob Forrest, \'Bob and the Monster\' available on iTunes now <a href=\" https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/bob-and-the-monster/id685583635\">here</a>.\n<div class=\"embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9\"><iframe class=\"embed-responsive-item\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/LD8tb_wx18w\" width=\"460\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2>Running with Monsters: A Memoir</strong></h2>\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-283\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Running-with-Monsters-250x378.jpg\" alt=\"Running with Monsters\" /><strong>Celebrity Rehab star and Thelonious Monster frontman Bob Forrest\'s memoir about his drug-fueled life in the L.A. indie rock scene of the \'80s and \'90s and his life-changing decision to become a drug counselor who specializes in \"reaching the unreachable.\"</strong>\n\nLife has been one strange trip for Bob Forrest.  He started out as a suburban teenage drunkard from the Southern California suburbs and went on to become a member of a hip Hollywood crowd that included the Red Hot Chili Peppers, Johnny Depp, and River Phoenix.  Los Angeles was their playground, and they hung out in such infamous haunts as the Viper Room and the Whisky a Go Go.\n\nAlways one to push things to their limit, Bob partied the hardest and could usually be found at the center of the drama.  Drugs weren’t Bob’s only passion.  He was also a talented musician who commanded the stage as the wild and unpredictable lead singer of Thelonious Monster.  They traveled the world, and their future seemed bright and wide open.  But Bob’s demons grew stronger as he achieved more success and he sank deeper into his chemical dependency, which included alcohol, crack, and heroin habits.  No matter how many times he went to rehab, sobriety just wouldn’t stick for him.  Soon he saw his once-promising music career slip away entirely.\n\nEventually, Bob found a way to defeat his addiction, and once he did, he saw the opportunity to help other hopeless cases by becoming a certified drug counselor.  He’s helped addicts from all walks of life, often employing methods that are very much at odds with the traditional rehab approach.\n\nRunning with Monsters is an electrifying chronicle of the LA rock scene of the 1980s and ’90s, the story of a man who survived and triumphed over his demons, and a controversial perspective on the rehab industry and what it really takes to beat addiction. Bob tells his story with unflinching honesty and hard-won perspective, making this a reading experience that shocks, entertains, and ultimately inspires.\n\nThe book can be purchased on Amazon <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Running-Monsters-Memoir-Bob-Forrest/dp/077043598X\">here</a>.\n','A Message From Bob Forrest','','publish','open','open','','a-message-from-bob-forrest','','','2013-11-08 20:49:44','2013-11-08 20:49:44','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=219',35,'page','',0),(221,1,'2013-11-08 20:49:54','2013-11-08 20:49:54','Situated on a rare and beautiful Equestrian Estate, our main house is special from the moment you pass through the gates on to the enchanted tree-lined drive leading to our home.  As you pass the riding arena, stables, sensational rose gardens, and climb up to the large knoll that is the site of Alo House, all you can see is sweeping views of Malibu\'s famed Zuma Beach.  Walls of glass frame the sunny home, where each enormous room seamlessly flows into the next.\n\nAll rooms open to the ocean view and breeze, including a dedicated yoga and meditation studio.  A professional chef’s kitchen and dining area is at the heart of the home, where hot, home cooked meals are shared around a gigantic family table.  Alo House is located in the exclusive \'Malibu Park\' neighborhood, and has access to wonderful close-by amenities, all within minutes away:  miles of State Parkland hiking and trail riding, Zuma and Broad Beaches, many eateries and the brand-new Trancas Market Center.\n\nWe show our clients that a life without drugs and alcohol is far from over. Quite the contrary, it has really just begun! We offer our clients a warm, small-scale family environment. The sense of community at Alo House is like no other treatment center. We cultivate and nurture our clients’ sense of self-esteem, confidence, joy, and belonging.\n<h3>Inclusive Amenities and Services:</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Access to the most beautiful beaches in Southern California</li>\n	<li>Large flat-screen TVs in each luxuriously appointed guest room</li>\n	<li>Gourmet, chef-prepared breakfast lunch and dinner, seven days a week, plus unlimited snack foods</li>\n	<li>Jacuzzi</li>\n	<li>Outdoor BBQ area</li>\n	<li>Surfing</li>\n	<li>Gym memberships</li>\n	<li>Yoga and meditation on-site</li>\n	<li>Hiking</li>\n	<li>Guided meditation</li>\n	<li>Housekeeping services</li>\n	<li>Transportation to appointments</li>\n	<li>Numerous nearby volunteer opportunities</li>\n</ul>','Amenities','','publish','open','open','','amenities','','','2013-11-08 20:49:54','2013-11-08 20:49:54','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=221',34,'page','',0),(245,1,'2013-11-11 00:38:13','2013-11-11 00:38:13','','jessica_kauffman','','inherit','open','open','','jessica_kauffman-2','','','2013-11-11 00:38:13','2013-11-11 00:38:13','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/jessica_kauffman1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(246,1,'2013-11-11 01:13:02','2013-11-11 01:13:02','If you have health insurance, please enter your information below to allow us to do a free verification of benefits to determine your out-of-pocket costs for your stay.  ALL INFORMATION YOU SUBMIT IS CONFIDENTIAL:\n\n[gravityform id=\"2\" name=\"Verify Your Insurance\" title=\"false\" description=\"false\"]','Verify Your Insurance','','publish','open','open','','verify-your-insurance','','','2013-11-11 01:13:02','2013-11-11 01:13:02','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?page_id=246',33,'page','',0),(258,1,'2013-11-11 05:03:06','2013-11-11 05:03:06','','bob-main-picture','','inherit','open','open','','bob-main-picture','','','2013-11-11 05:03:06','2013-11-11 05:03:06','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/bob-main-picture.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(262,1,'2013-07-31 06:53:56','2013-07-31 06:53:56','We love our friends at Paradigm Malibu Adolescent Treatment Center. Jeff Nalin and his staff do it right! Like us, they have found great success in a non-punitive, non-compliance-based approach to treatment. And they treat the emotional disturbances that underlie their clients\' behaviors, rather than just the behavior itself. Furthermore, Paradigm provides their clients with the kind of loving, supportive environment that empowers them. Both Alo House and Paradigm strive to build our clients up, rather than tear them down.\n\n<address><strong>par·a·digm</strong></address><address>/ˈparəˌdīm/</address>\n<div>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><address>Noun</address>\n<div>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ol>\n	<li><address>One that serves as a pattern or model.</address></li>\n	<li><address>A set of assumptions, concepts, values, and practices that constitutes a way of viewing reality for the community that shares them.</address></li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\nParadigm Malibu takes a totally new approach to adolescent treatment.  But don\'t take our word for it. Visit their website, <a title=\"Paradigm Malibu\" href=\"http://www.paradigmmalibu.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.paradigmmalibu.com</a>, watch their video below, and see for yourself!\n\n</div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/8k2Iyyg7_WI?feature=player_embedded\" height=\"420\" width=\"710\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>','Meet Our Friends at \'Paradigm Malibu\'','','publish','open','open','','meet-our-friends-at-paradigm-malibu','','','2013-07-31 06:53:56','2013-07-31 06:53:56','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?p=262',87,'post','',0),(265,1,'2013-06-29 06:55:43','2013-06-29 06:55:43','Alo House is pleased to announce the unveiling of our exciting new organic farm project. Perched over the majestic pacific ocean, Alo House Farms sits on over six acres of lush, fertile land. So far, we have built twenty 16\'x4\' raised beds, brimming with rich organic soil. Future plans include an orchard, and livestock. We have adopted six chickens, who will soon be joined by pigmy goats and ducks.\n\n<a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2227.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-307\" alt=\"IMG_2227\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2227.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a>\n\nWe are growing tomatoes, peppers, eggplants, asparagus, onions, herbs and more!\n\n<a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2224.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-306\" alt=\"IMG_2224\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2224.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a>\n\nThe entire farm project, and future product line -- marketed under the Alo House Farms banner -- is meant to provide our clients with community economic development opportunities. Not only will Alo House Farms provide clients with a source of income and work experience, whether it\'s in marketing, horticulture, administration, but just as important, it will give them a sense of self-esteem and build confidence in their ability to contribute to society in a meaningful way.\n\n<a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2221.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-305\" alt=\"IMG_2221\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2221.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a>\n\nAdditionally, by selling the products in the local marketplace, in stores and at the Malibu farmer\'s market, the Alo House Farms project will work to remove the stigma attached to addiction, and to the recovery community in Malibu more generally. Local citizens will be able to see us for who we really are -- a close-knit community of good hearted young people who just needed to feel passionate about something, plus a little support and guidance.\n\nHere are some more photos of the farm:\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/farm-work-party.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-316\" alt=\"farm work party\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/farm-work-party-300x300.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/kaya-on-farm.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-317\" alt=\"kaya on farm\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/kaya-on-farm-300x300.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2232.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-308\" alt=\"IMG_2232\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2232.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2233.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-309\" alt=\"IMG_2233\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2233.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2234.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-310\" alt=\"IMG_2234\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2234.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2235.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-311\" alt=\"IMG_2235\" src=\"https://alorecovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/IMG_2235.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>','Introducing, Alo House Farms!','','publish','open','open','','introducing-acadia-farms','','','2013-06-29 06:55:43','2013-06-29 06:55:43','',0,'http://dev.alorecovery.com/?p=265',86,'post','',0),(283,1,'2013-11-21 19:33:11','2013-11-21 19:33:11','','Running with Monsters','','inherit','closed','open','','running-with-monsters','','','2013-11-21 19:33:11','2013-11-21 19:33:11','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Running-with-Monsters.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(290,1,'2013-11-21 21:08:43','2013-11-21 21:08:43','','caroline-bentley','','inherit','closed','open','','caroline-bentley','','','2013-11-21 21:08:43','2013-11-21 21:08:43','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/caroline-bentley.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(293,1,'2013-11-27 20:29:12','2013-11-27 20:29:12','','As seen on a Sussex Directories Inc site','','inherit','closed','open','','as-seen-on-a-sussex-directories-inc-site','','','2013-11-27 20:29:12','2013-11-27 20:29:12','',0,'http://alohouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/130694_2_120x150-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(294,1,'2013-11-27 20:31:49','2013-11-27 20:31:49','','Therapick-IrisNathanielMFTTherapistEncinoCA954-439','','inherit','closed','open','','therapick-irisnathanielmfttherapistencinoca954-439','','','2013-11-27 20:31:49